fields.event_title: LunarXP Sets Target for First Mars Landing in 2030
fields.post_intro: LunarXP is thrilled to announce the next chapter in its journey across the our solar system: MarsXP.
fields.post_content:
The Red Planet has fascinated both astrophysicists and sci-fi fans for decades – but today, we're closer than ever to visiting and living on Mars. LunarXP is thrilled to announce the next chapter in its journey across the our solar system: MarsXP.

This exciting new chapter will leverage the vast network of LunarXP resources as a "jumping off" point for reaching Mars in the next two to five years. The initiative will begin with a orbital lab and docking station for planetary colonization. Using the same template for colonization as the LunarXP program, MarsXP will build a network of critical stations for scientific and resource development initiatives.

fields.event_title: New Spending Bill Expands Funding for Space Exploration
fields.post_intro: The new bill gives LunarXP a decade-long budget to fulfill the mission of space exploration.
fields.post_content:
LunarXP is proud to partner with the National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) on a fiscal omnibus bill to fund critical government services on the moon's surface. In the groundbreaking bill, Congress and the President have given significant funding to help ensure national security and exploration interested through the private company, providing additional resources to fund mining and scientific initiatives that will give the United States access to "astro fuels" and new forms of energy.

The bill, which was just signed on Monday, will provide funding through the next decade. While NASA has traditionally shouldered much of the space services involved, LunarXP has provided a free market option that saves tax payers significantly over the long term and helps advance the private sector's interests in space industries.

The bill also includes additional dollars for roadmapping a Mars initiative in the next five years. LunarXP has already launched a new initiative – MarsXP – to service this program, and plans to have its first landing site and Martian orbital platform by late next year.

fields.event_title: LunarXP Wins  Space Innovator of the Year Award
fields.post_intro: LunarXP has won a prestigious award for its participation in a variety of cosmic explorations.
fields.post_content:
(Cape Canaveral, FL) LunarXP, the leader in moon exploration and colonization, is proud to announce that it is the recipient of the prestigious "Space Innovator of the Year" Award. This marks the third year in a row that the private interstellar travel and resource development organization has received the distinction.

"We're thrilled to be honored by the international space community once again this year," said Shane Morrison, Chief Space Officer of LunarXP and commander of the moon-based container fleet. "This company was founded on a dream: to explore the stars. Together, we've been able to make that dream a reality and turn this mission into a commercially viable enterprise. We look forward to continuing our exploration to Mars and beyond in the coming years."

LunarXP is running daily flights from Cape Canaveral, FL and San Jose, CA to the orbiting XPlatform, where multiple Lunar XPlorer vessels ferry passengers to a growing number of lunar habitats. LunarXP is currently hiring specialists in a number of key areas for part- and full-time employment in their permanent moon settlements.

"Not only is LunarXP exploring new worlds, but our scientists are developing new technologies that are impacting the earth's reliance on fossil fuels and renewable energy sources," said Morrison. "We're mining new types of metals and minerals that have unlimited applications across industries. We excited to be sharing our discoveries with the world."

fields.heading_title: An Engaging Online Experience For Job Seekers And Others In The Field Of Design.
fields.post_content:
Logic is one of the leading talent recruitment and outplacement firms for the architecture, interior design, engineering and manufacturing industries. The focus of Logic's business is talent recruitment and placement so security is a high priority in order to protect the confidential nature of the job search process. That's one reason Solodev CMS's secure content management software was the right choice for this project.

A dynamic jobs portal integrates with Logic's applicant tracking system and the multi-segmented blog allows visitors to select their areas of interest. A slider manager allows Logic staff to easily keep the site looking fresh with new homepages visuals.
